						               													<description>Con6 is a unique game that combines elements of thinking, strategy and luck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of the game:&amp;#10;To be the first to form a sequence of 6 &amp;ldquo;riders&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game parts:&amp;#10;1) 24 triangular &amp;ldquo;bases&amp;rdquo; (large) &amp;ndash; 12 per color.&amp;#10;2) 24 triangular &amp;ldquo;riders&amp;rdquo; (small) &amp;ndash; 12 per color.&amp;#10;3) Game bag. &amp;#10;4) Playing instructions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Preparations for the game:&amp;#10;1) Each player chooses his color.&amp;#10;2) Each player places the 12 riders in the chosen color next to him.&amp;#10;3) The bases of both colors are inserted into the game bag and thoroughly mixed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Course of play:&amp;#10;1) The younger player randomly draws a base out of the bag. The person whose color is the same as the base that has been drawn begins. The drawn base is returned to the bag.&amp;#10;2) Each player randomly draws one base from the bag and places it beside him, so that it is visible to both players.&amp;#10;3) The first player places his base on the table and randomly draws a new base from the bag. It is now the other player&amp;rsquo;s turn, and so on.&amp;#10;4) Each player, in his turn, can place a rider on a vacant base or place a new base next to an existing one, in accordance with the game rules. &amp;#10;If a player chooses to place a base, he randomly draws a new base from the bag and places it beside him, so that it is visible to both players.  &amp;#10; Winning the game:&amp;#10;The winner is the player who manages to form a sequence of 6 riders of his own color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
